Academic References
-------------------

The SPADL action representation and data format conventions follow:
Decroos, T. et al. (2019). "Actions Speak Louder than Goals: Valuing
Player Actions in Soccer." Proceedings of the 25th ACM SIGKDD.

The Expected Possession Value (EPV) framework and counterfactual
evaluation methodology are described in:
Kim, H. et al. (2026). "Better Prevent than Tackle: Valuing Defense
in Soccer Based on Graph Neural Networks." MIT Sloan Sports Analytics
Conference. See: https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.10355

Event-tracking data synchronization references:
Kim, H. et al. (2025). "ELASTIC: Event-Level Alignment of Synchronized
Tracking and InferCed data." See: https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.09238
